(146, 1, '2015-09-22 07:21:43', '2015-09-22 07:21:43', '<img src="http://130.56.251.93/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/FLLBanner.jpg" alt="" />\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><em>FIRST</em> LEGO League (FLL®) is a competition catering for upper-primary and lower-secondary school students. Every year, teams of up to 10 students build, program and compete with a robot, while also learning about a modern problem in science and engineering and developing solutions for it.  The entire competition for the year is based around one of these themes: Past themes include natural disasters, senior citizens, food health &amp; safety, climate change, medical science, and nanotechnology.  Tournaments are run with the feel of a sporting event, and teams compete like crazy while having the time of their lives.  What FLL teams accomplish is nothing short of amazing. It’s fun. It’s exciting. And the skills they learn will last a lifetime.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3><span style="color: #333399;">Requirements and Cost</span></h3>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><em>FIRST</em> LEGO League is an incredibly rewarding program for young students, and teams can come from schools, social groups, community groups, homes, church groups, etc.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">If you want to start a team, there are a few things you’ll need:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A dedicated adult coach</li>\r\n	<li>A LEGO Mindstorms EV3, NXT or RCX robot kit</li>\r\n	<li>A place to meet to work on building robots, practicing games and working on the project.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Registering a team for Australian competitions costs AUD$350 for one team with one kit, or AUD$425 for two teams sharing one kit.  This registration cost includes a competition challenge set for the team to practice with, and the right to compete at a regional qualifying tournament.  If the team performs well, they may be invited to compete at a national level for no extra registration cost.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong><span style="color: #333399;">To register a team for the 2015-2016 Season, Trash Trek, please go to</span> <a title="FIRST Australia Registration" href="http://www.firstaustralia.org/systems/">firstaustralia.org/systems/</a>.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3><span style="color: #333399;">Practice Kits</span></h3>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">FLL practice kits from previous seasons are available at a discounted rate.  These kits are useful between seasons for new teams who would like to learn the game and develop robot strategies before the new season is released (generally in August of each year).   If you would like to purchase a “practice kit”, please complete this <a href="http://firstaustralia.science.mq.edu.au/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Practice-Set-Order-Form.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>ORDER FORM </strong></a><em>(clickable link)</em> and email to: <a href="mailto:wynonah.bush@mq.edu.au" target="_blank">wynonah.bush@mq.edu.au </a>.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3><span style="color: #333399;"><strong><em>FIRST LEGO League Regional Contacts</em></strong></span></h3>\r\n<div class="well">\r\n<ul class="list-unstyled">\r\n	<li><span style="color: #333399;"><strong>Adelaide</strong>:</span> Wendy Gomersall (<a title="info@concept2creation.com.au" href="mailto:info@concept2creation.com.au" target="_blank">@concept2creation.com.au</a>)</li>\r\n	<li><span style="color: #333399;"><strong>Brisbane, QUT Precincts (The Cube)</strong>: </span>Jacina Leong (<a href="https://firstaustralia.org/start-fll-team/thecube@qut.edu.au">thecube@qut.edu.au</a>)</li>\r\n	<li><span style="color: #333399;"><strong>Brisbane, QUT Caboolture</strong>:</span> Chris Chalmers (<a href="mailto:c.chalmers@qut.edu.au" target="_blank">c.chalmers@qut.edu.au</a>)</li>\r\n	<li><span style="color: #333399;"><strong>Brisbane,  Grace Lutheran College</strong>:</span>  Peter Kellett (<a href="mailto:peter_kellett@glc.qld.edu.au" target="_blank">peter_kellett@glc.qld.edu.au</a>)</li>\r\n	<li><span style="color: #333399;"><strong>Perth</strong>:</span><strong> </strong>Tim Keely (<a href="mailto:T.Keely@curtin.edu.au" target="_blank">T.Keely@curtin.edu.au</a>)</li>\r\n	<li><span style="color: #333399;"><strong>Melbourne</strong>:</span> Therese Keane (<a href="mailto:tkeane@swin.edu.au">tkeane@swin.edu.au</a>)</li>\r\n	<li><span style="color: #333399;"><strong>Sydney</strong>:</span> Fred Westling (<a href="mailto:fred@firstaustralia.org">fred@firstaustralia.org</a>)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<img src="http://firstaustralia.science.mq.edu.au/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/HOLD-ON-1024x1024.png" alt="" />', 'Start a FLL Team', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'start-a-fll-team', '', '', '2015-10-14 14:40:31', '2015-10-14 14:40:31', '', 98, 'http://130.56.251.93/?page_id=146', 0, 'page', '', 0),
