(427, 1, '2015-10-14 04:35:56', '2015-10-14 04:35:56', '<header class="post-header">\r\n<h1 class="entry-title"><span style="color: #000080;">LEGO Education Conference with Chris Rogers</span></h1>\r\n<time class="published" datetime="2015-02-16T15:14:08+00:00">February 16, 2015</time>\r\n\r\n</header>\r\n<div class="entry-content">\r\n\r\n<strong>Professor Chris Rogers has been invited to Australia to work with Primary and Secondary teachers interested in making use of LEGO materials to support learning across the Australian Curriculum (STEM and Humanities).  He will be the keynote speaker during the opening ceremony of the FRC Australia Regional at Sydney Olympic Park – Sports Centre on Friday, 13 March 2015.</strong>\r\n\r\n<a href="https://firstaustralia.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/Chris-Rogers.jpg"><img class=" size-full wp-image-915 aligncenter" src="https://firstaustralia.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/Chris-Rogers.jpg" alt="Chris Rogers" width="200" height="268" /></a>\r\n\r\nThe day will begin at 8:30 am at the Sydney Olympic Park – Sports Centre during the <a href="http://firstaustralia.org/frc-regional-2015/" target="_blank"><strong>FRC Australia Regional </strong></a>with a keynote presentation <strong>followed by the first one hour hands-on workshop for teachers. </strong>\r\n\r\nFollowing the teachers workshops, students may participate in a one hour workshop and stay to watch the FRC competition in the arena.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Limit 30 students per session</li>\r\n	<li>5 students per school</li>\r\n	<li>Years 5-8</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThere are two student sessions:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>10:45 am</li>\r\n	<li>12:45 pm</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nChris Rogers will lead the participants through a series of fun and engaging design challenges that are relevant to a wide range of age-groups.\r\n\r\nThe purpose of the LEGO Education Conference is to gather teachers and educators who use or plan to use LEGO materials in their classroom in order to:\r\n\r\n– try out activities that a relevant to the Australian Curriculum\r\n– share experiences and ideas for implementing these approaches in the classroom with colleagues\r\n\r\nTo register for any of the three workshops, please email <a href="mailto:wynonah.bush@mq.edu.au">wynonah.bush@mq.edu.au</a> with your school information and teachers attending.  For those bringing students, please indicate which session you would prefer to attend and the number of students (limit 5 per school) attending.  Sessions are first-come, first-serve and will fill fast.\r\n\r\n</div>', 'LEGO Education Conference with Chris Rogers', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'lego-education-conference-with-chris-rogers', '', '', '2015-10-14 04:36:04', '2015-10-14 04:36:04', '', 107, 'http://130.56.251.93/?page_id=427', 0, 'page', '', 0),
