(448, 1, '2015-10-14 14:36:39', '2015-10-14 14:36:39', '<div class="wrap container">\r\n<div class="content row">\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<img src="https://firstaustralia.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Web_banner-graphic2.png" alt="" width="725" height="900" />\r\n\r\n<h3><span style="color: #333399;">Who is teaching my Child?</span></h3>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Our RoboCamps are run with upmost professionalism and fun. Our camps are run by Macquarie University students, or members of the <a href="http://www.thethunderdownunder.org/">Thunder Down Under</a> robotics team. We want to make sure your child is safe and having fun at all times. With Macquarie University covering all bases, your child is in excellent hands! All 18+ camp facilitators have working with children checks and go through training to ensure they understand the right course of action, should an incident occur.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">We encourage parents who have any concerns to please feel free to contact the RoboCamps coordinator – James McArthur. Mob: 0432 853 961.</p>\r\n<img src="https://firstaustralia.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Photos_website1.png" alt="" width="800" height="533" />\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3><span style="color: #333399;">Locations</span></h3>\r\n</div>\r\nRoboCamps are run out of Macquarie University’s Department of Engineering and FIRST Australia. These camps are located in building E6A, on the second floor. More information about rooms etc. is given upon registration; as they are subject to change throughout the year. Our facilities are held in safe, secure rooms – with bathrooms and bubblers near-by for safe and secure access. Your children are our number one priority.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h3><span style="color: #333399;">Payment and Registration</span></h3>\r\nFollow the links to register for the camps. Extra information in relation to the camp will be sent out upon registration.\r\n\r\nIf you have difficulties with registration, or do not receive a 